als writers who can use the research findings to improve the practice of teaching and learning speaking in the language classroom.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aCommunicative competencexStudy and teaching. 0aIntercultural communicationxStudy and teaching. 0aLanguage and culture. 0aLanguage and languagesxStudy and teaching. 0aSecond language acquisition. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Study & Teaching.2bisacsh  aEFL.  aL2.  aSLA.  aWTC.  aWillingness to communicate.  acommunicative behaviour.  aforeign language acquisition.  aindividual differences.  aindividual learner differences.  ainstructed second language acquisition.  amotivation.  asecond language acquisition.  ateaching and learning speaking.1 aPawlak, Mirosław, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066312908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters eBook Package 2015-2017z978311060670640uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978178309717340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781783097173423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781783097173/original  a978-3-11-060670-6  MultiLingual Matters eBook Package 2015-2017c2015d2017  a978-3-11-066312-9  MultiLingual Matters Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK